-> Numeric Data Types: 
    INT → Stores numbers.
    TINYINT → Small integer (0 to 255 or -128 to 127).
    BIGINT → Large integer values.
    FLOAT / DOUBLE
    DECIMAL(p, s) → Exact decimal values
        p = Total number of digits
        s = Number of digits after the decimal point.
        Example:
            DECIMAL(10,2) -> 12345678.90



-> String Data Types
    VARCHAR(n) → Variable-length text.
    CHAR(n) → Fixed-length text.
    TEXT → Large text data.



-> Date & Time Data Types
    DATE → Stores dates (YYYY-MM-DD).
    DATETIME → Stores date & time (YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS).
    TIMESTAMP → Stores date & time (automatically updates on changes).
    TIME → Stores only time (HH:MM:SS).



-> Boolean Data Type
    BOOLEAN → Stores 0(false) or 1(true).